AddLeaderboardAccessPermission.name: AddLeaderboardAccessPermission
AddLeaderboardAccessPermission.documentation:
Join a community race.

Using this method you can join the race without having to open the AWS DeepRacer Console.

When successful, the leaderboard for a given race will be available to you in the leaderboards list

CloneReinforcementLearningModel.name: CloneReinforcementLearningModel
CloneReinforcementLearningModel.documentation: Clones an existing model and continues training with new instructions

CreateAccountResources.name: CreateAccountResources
CreateAccountResources.documentation: This method is no longer supported and should not be used.

CreateCar.name: CreateCar
CreateCar.documentation:
Create a new car to train your model with.

You can choose various settings for your car including the action space, name or look.

There is a limit of 20 cars that you can create. If you reach this limit, update an existing car instead using update-car

CreateLeaderboardAccessToken.name: CreateLeaderboardAccessToken
CreateLeaderboardAccessToken.documentation:
Create a new invitation token for the community race. It is useful if your existing invitation link has been shared outside of your desired users.

To use the new token simply put it in place of [token] in url https://console.aws.amazon.com/deepracer/home#raceToken/[token]

Creation of a new access token makes the old token invalid.

CreateLeaderboardSubmission.name: CreateLeaderboardSubmission
CreateLeaderboardSubmission.documentation:
Submit a model to a race.

Simply choose the model and a race and your submission will be created

When creating your first submission you need to confirm that you accept the terms and conditions of it. If you don't, you will not be allowed to submit your entry.

CreateReinforcementLearningModel.name: CreateReinforcementLearningModel
CreateReinforcementLearningModel.documentation:
Starts a new training with instructions provided.

A new model is created and used in the training session to gather experiences, then it is updated in the learning session based on the reward gathered.

While you can start training through the cli/boto3, it is recommended that you use the Deepracer Console instead for a richer experience.

DeleteAccountResources.name: DeleteAccountResources
DeleteAccountResources.documentation: This method is no longer supported and should not be used.

DeleteCar.name: DeleteCar
DeleteCar.documentation: This method is for internal use only and should not be used.

DeleteCars.name: DeleteCars
DeleteCars.documentation: This method is for internal use only and should not be used.

DeleteModel.name: DeleteModel
DeleteModel.documentation:
Delete existing model.

This method lets you limit your AWS DeepRacer model storage costs

GetAccountResources.name: GetAccountResources
GetAccountResources.documentation: This method is no longer supported and should not be used.

GetAlias.name: GetAlias
GetAlias.documentation: Displays the racer alias assigned to given account

GetAssetUrl.name: GetAssetUrl
GetAssetUrl.documentation:
Used to fetch various assets related to a model, training or race submission

Returns a Url that you can use to fetch things like logs, models etc.

Asset types prefixed with "S3_" are for copying assets to S3 (operations available in a model view under Actions->Copy to S3).

GetEvaluation.name: GetEvaluation
GetEvaluation.documentation:
Get evaluation details.

Returns information about a given evaluation

GetLatestUserSubmission.name: GetLatestUserSubmission
GetLatestUserSubmission.documentation:
Returns information about the most recent model submission status

This is the information that you will see next to your name on the race page.

GetLeaderboard.name: GetLeaderboard
GetLeaderboard.documentation:
Returns a details for a race

Does not return the entrants ranking - that is available through ListLeaderboardSubmissions (list-leaderboard-submissions for AWS CLI).

GetPrivateLeaderboard.name: GetPrivateLeaderboard
GetPrivateLeaderboard.documentation:
Returns a details for a race

Don't quote me on that but it does look like an aliast for GetLeaderboard (get-leaderboard) which returns both community and public leaderboards

Does not return the entrants ranking - that is available through ListLeaderboardSubmissions (list-leaderboard-submissions for AWS CLI).

GetRankedUserSubmission.name: GetRankedUserSubmission
GetRankedUserSubmission.documentation: Returns current user's best submission for a given race.

GetTrainingJob.name: GetTrainingJob
GetTrainingJob.documentation: Get information about how a model is being trained

ImportModel.name: ImportModel
ImportModel.documentation:
Import a model from S3 into console

Allows to import a model from backup or alternative training solution and clone for more training or submit to a race.

ListEvaluations.name: ListEvaluations
ListEvaluations.documentation: Returns a list of evaluations performed on a given model.

ListLeaderboardSubmissions.name: ListLeaderboardSubmissions
ListLeaderboardSubmissions.documentation: Returns an ordered list of a given race entries.

ListLeaderboards.name: ListLeaderboards
ListLeaderboards.documentation: List races that current user has access to

ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants.name: ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants
ListPrivateLeaderboardParticipants.documentation:
Lists users which have joined a private race.

For public race Arn an empty list is returned

ListPrivateLeaderboards.name: ListPrivateLeaderboards
ListPrivateLeaderboards.documentation: Lists community races that current user has created.

ListSubscribedPrivateLeaderboards.name: ListSubscribedPrivateLeaderboards
ListSubscribedPrivateLeaderboards.documentation: Lists community races that current user has joined.

ListTrainingJobs.name: ListTrainingJobs
ListTrainingJobs.documentation:
List current user's training jobs

Training jobs are associated with models that user has.

MigrateModels.name: MigrateModels
MigrateModels.documentation: This method is no longer be relevant and you should not use it

RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission.name: RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission
RemoveLeaderboardAccessPermission.documentation: Removes a racer from a community race administrated by the current user.

SetAlias.name: SetAlias
SetAlias.documentation:
Set your racer name. You can only set your racer name once so choose wisely!

The names are checked in terms approprietness. You may have your name rejected if a disallowed word is a substring of it.

StartEvaluation.name: StartEvaluation
StartEvaluation.documentation:
Evaluate your model in conditions of your choice.

This is a great opportunity to check how your model is doing without the entropy altering it actions which happens during the training. But there's more: you can try a different track, different racing format or even race your model against a car with another model that you have trained.

StopEvaluation.name: StopEvaluation
StopEvaluation.documentation:
Stop performing evaluation

The system will still take some time to shut everything down, but the evaluation will have been stopped at the time of request

StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel.name: StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel
StopTrainingReinforcementLearningModel.documentation:
Stop the training job.

The training will be immediately interrupted and will perform a shutdown of the environment which can take a few minutes. Once done, you will be able to evaluate, clone or submit your model to a race. The interrupted iteration is discarded and only the last and the best complete iterations are being stored.

TestRewardFunction.name: TestRewardFunction
TestRewardFunction.documentation:
Test reward function. Submit your function to perform a number of tests against it.

Not all problems are clearly communicated even if caught, for instance whitespace issues. If you don't get the details that could help you, do revert to a code editor of your choice.

UpdateCar.name: UpdateCar
UpdateCar.documentation:
Change settings of your car

You can choose various settings for your car including the action space, name or look.

Changing the settings for a car only affects new models being created from scratch. Old models and their clones will continue to use the old settings which are stored with the model at the start of a new training and then passed on during cloning.

ModelArnToClone.documentation: Identifies the base model that you wish to clone

ModelName.documentation: The name that you want to give to your new model

ModelDescription.documentation: Descirption that you want to give to your new model

TrainingConfig.documentation: Configuration of the training to be started after cloning

RoleArn.documentation: Arn Role of the user that allows to perform this operation

AutoSubmission.documentation: Decide whether after training completion you wish to submit the model to a race

CloneReinforcementLearningModelResponse.documentation: Identifies the model that has been created

Name.documentation: A name to be given to imported model

RoleArn.documentation: An Arn of a role that current user has assigned, which allows to fetch files from that bucket

documentation:
AWS DeepRacer is the easiest way to get started with learning reinforcement learning. Visit https://aws.amazon.com/deepracer/ to learn more.

While it is strongly recommended that you start interacting with DeepRacer through the AWS Console, all operations available on the website are also available programatically and through aws cli.
